  Schema: Work_request_arm
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm"/>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Type: affected_item_select 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.affected_item_select"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Activity_method_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment">
An <b>Activity_method_assignment</b> is an association between an <express_ref
linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/> 
and a <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>. 
The <b>relation_type</b> attribute characterizes the meaning of that association and the meaning of the <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/>

 with respect to the <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Activity_method_assignment  Attribute: assigned_method 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment.assigned_method"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment.assigned_method">
the <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/> 
that is associated.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Activity_method_assignment  Attribute: associated_request 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment.associated_request"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment.associated_request">
the <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> that is considered.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Activity_method_assignment  Attribute: relation_type 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment.relation_type"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description
linkend="Work_request_arm.Activity_method_assignment.relation_type">
  <p>
    the text that identifies the nature of the relationship between the 
    <express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/> 
    and the <express_ref
linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>.
  </p>
<p>Where applicable, the following values shall be used:</p>
<ul>
<li>
'recommended method': the 
<express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/> 
is the recommended approach to accomplish the requested work;</li>
<li>
'non recommended method': the 
<express_ref linkend="activity_method:arm:Activity_method_arm.Activity_method"/> 
should not be used to accomplish the requested work.</li>
</ul>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Affected_items_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Affected_items_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Affected_items_assignment">
An <b>Affected_items_assignment</b> is an association of a <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> with 
the product or activity data that are subjects of this <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>.
<example>
    In case a tire on a car is flat, a <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> may be created and associated with the instances that represent the tire
    that is flat, the car and the spare wheel.
  </example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Affected_items_assignment  Attribute: assigned_work_request 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Affected_items_assignment.assigned_work_request"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Affected_items_assignment.assigned_work_request">
the <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> for which a set of items is being identified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Affected_items_assignment  Attribute: items 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Affected_items_assignment.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Affected_items_assignment.items">
the set of things that are affected by the <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request  
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request">
A <b>Work_request</b> is the solicitation for some work to be done. 
<note>
These requests may not be acted upon depending
on the authorization granted to the request or its associated
<express_ref linkend="work_order:arm:Work_order_arm.Work_order"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request  Attribute: request_id 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request.request_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request.request_id">
the identification that distinguishes the <b>Work_request</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request  Attribute: version_id 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request.version_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request.version_id">
the identification of the version of the <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>.
The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request  Attribute: purpose 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request.purpose"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request.purpose"><p>the 
text that describes the reason for the activity request.</p>
<example number="2">
'technical improvement',
'government regulation', 'durability improvement', 'tool improvement', 'production relief', 'production
requirement', 'quality improvement', 'security reason', 'standardization', 'cost reduction', 'customer rejection' in case the request results from a rejection by a customer,
'change of standard', 'production alignment', and 'procurement alignment' are examples of purpose.
</example>
</ext_description>

<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request.description"><p>the 
text that provides further information about the <b>Work_request</b>. 
The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</p>
<example number="1">This attribute may contain a description of the issue that was the origin of the request.</example>
</ext_description>

<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request_relationship 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request.request_id"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_relationship">
  A <b>Work_request_relationship</b> is a relationship between two 
  <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> 
  objects. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_relationship.relation_type">
  <p>specifies the meaning of the relationship.</p>
  <p>Where applicable the following values shall be used:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>'dependency': The <b>related</b> 
      <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> 
      is dependent of the <b>relating</b> 
      <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>.
      </li>
  </ul>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_relationship.description">
  specifies additional information.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_relationship.relating">
  specifies the first of the two 
  <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> 
  objects.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_relationship.related">
  specifies the second of the two 
  <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> 
  objects.
</ext_description>


<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request_status  
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request_status"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_status">
A <b>Work_request_status</b> is an association of a status with 
a <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/>.
<note>A 
  <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> may have zero or more statuses, assigned at various dates by various organizations.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request_status  Attribute: status 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request_status.status"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_status.status">
  <p>
    the text that provides a user interpretable designation for the level of completion   
    of the study and resolution of the work request.
  </p>
  <example>
'drafted', 'issued', 'deferred', 'in-hand', 'completed', 'cancelled', 'rejected' are examples of request status.
  </example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Work_request_arm  Entity: Work_request_status  Attribute: work_request 
   <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request_status.work_request"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Work_request_arm.Work_request_status.work_request">
the <express_ref linkend="work_request:arm:Work_request_arm.Work_request"/> to which the status applies.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
